Global Cassava Leaves Market Insights
Cassava Leaves Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Cassava Leaves Market Overview
The global cassava leaves market has seen steady growth, with a market value estimated at USD 6.9 billion in 2024, expected to grow at a CAGR of 6.5% through 2030. This growth is driven by increased awareness of the health benefits of cassava leaves, their nutritional content, and their use in diverse cuisines across regions, particularly in Africa, Asia, and Latin America. Cassava leaves are rich in protein, fiber, vitamins, and minerals, which makes them a valuable ingredient in the food, pharmaceutical, and cosmetics industries. As demand rises for healthy and plant-based food options, the market is poised for continued expansion.

